content.htmlText:
We are in the middle of Pazari i Ri. The New Bazaar (Albanian: Pazari i Ri) is a neighbourhood in Tirana, Albania. The name of the neighbourhood stems from the groceries marketplace (the bazaar, in Albanian: pazar), which is situated in the area. It is located east of the central boulevard. Along with Mujos it forms part of the Old Town of Tirana and is one of the oldest areas of the city. The old historic Kokonozi Mosque of Ottoman times is situated here. The market offers a variety of fresh fruits, vegetables grown locally in the surrounding areas of Tirana, fish and meat, regional Albanian wine and raki. Many colorful buildings, restaurants and bakeries are surrounded. Recently, there have been a raising interest to make the Bazaar a touristic attraction. However in 2017, the bazaar were renovated and reconstructed.

The New Bazaar was built, before the reconstruction of 2016, in 1931 at the same place where the historic Old Bazaar were built, the latter extending up to present day Skanderbeg Square.

The apartment is five minutes' walking distance from Skanderbeg square. Seven minutes from Parliament, 10 - 15 minutes to main government buildings. 15 minutes from Blloku areas and from here you can easily reach all the main attractions of the city. 3 minutes from public transport or cabs.

section.about: We are a family of six persons and live in this neighborhood since ever. We have three young boys and our everyday life is all around them. I have a full time job, while my husband will be around to assist you in every need that you may have. We live in a building that is few steps away from you, meaning that we will be there for you whenever needed. We are always on standby in case of an emergency. Furthermore we respect your privacy and only interact if requested.

localizedReview.comments: The stay was wonderful, the apartment was great and Mia was very nice. We had to leave at 11:00, but we had the return flight at 19:00 and she was understanding and let us stay in the house until later, for €15 more, she was very considerate.

reviews.comments: "We had a wonderful stay at this House! The place was very clean and fully equipped with everything needed for a comfortable living experience. Its location is excellent—close to all major attractions, cafes, restaurants, and markets. The check-in and check-out process was seamless and hassle-free. The host was always available and responsive, making it easy to address any questions or concerns. Highly recommend this place for anyone visiting the area!"
Great stay

The place was clean, near some markets. a bit far to walk from rruga qemal stafa main street (especially when I brought suitcase) so a bit of hassle to go through the market road. but once I stayed and understand the neighborhood, i could just go via new bazaar street which was better access.
I had a good rest during my stay and i love it when i cook my own food for breakfast. thanks.
fantastic deal, beautiful lighting, comfy bed, great kitchen, and a fanTASTIC view from the balcony. I enjoyed watering the plants ^.^
We had a wonderful stay, thank you!

Ev sahibi ilgili ve sorulara hızlı yanıt veriyor. Evin balkonunda harika çiçekler bulunuyor. Sulamayı unutmayın. Yatak çok rahat ve temizdi. Ev genel olarak temizdi. Banyo ve mutfak gereçleri yeterli. Temiz havlu, tuvalet kağıdı, sabun bulunuyor. Bulaşık deterjanı, Islak mendil ve kağıt havlu gibi ihtiyaçlarınızı yanınızda getirmelisiniz. Tv ve wifi mevcut. Giyecekleri asabileceğiniz ve saklayabileceğiniz alanlar bulunuyor. Evin konumu harika bir noktada. Araç kiralayacaklar için evin bulunduğu sokakta park yeri mevcut. Ben genellikle geçe vakti park edip sabah erkenden çıktım. Uzun süreli parklarda garanti olsun derseniz TOPTANİ AVM otoparkını tercih edebilirsiniz.  İskender Bey meydanına 5 dk yürüme mesafesinde. Ulaşabileceğiniz her yere yakın diyebilirim. Talimatlarda her şey net şekilde anlatılmıştır. Bir arkadaşın tavsiyesi üzerine tercih etmiştik, iyi ki de tercih etmişiz. Memnun ayrılacağınızı düşünüyorum. Eşim ve ben memnun kaldık. Teşekkürler!

localizedReview.comments: The host is caring and responds quickly to questions. There are great flowers on the balcony of the house. Don't forget to water. The bed was very comfortable and clean. The house was generally clean. Bathroom and kitchen utensils are enough. There are clean towels, toilet paper, soap. You should bring your necessities such as dish soap, Wet wipes and paper towels. TV and wifi are available. There are areas where you can hang and store clothes. The location of the house is in a great spot. There is parking on the street where the house is located for those who will rent a car. I usually parked late and left early in the morning. If you want guarantee IN long-term parks, you can choose TOPTANI shopping mall parking.  5-min walk to Iskender Bey Square. I would say it is close to everywhere you can reach. Everything is clearly described in the instructions. We chose it on the advice of a friend, and we're glad we did. I think you will leave satisfied. My wife and I were satisfied. Thank you!

reviews.comments: I had a fantastic stay at Mia's place. Spacious, plenty of light, kitchen had what I needed and loved sitting out on the balcony. Was initially unsure of location, but it turned out to be great - walkable to everywhere, plenty of fruit and vegetable, meat and super markets nearby. Very homely base for my stay in Tirana.
Prettig, compleet, schoon appartement, ideale ligging. Winkels en restaurants cafés om de hoek. Alle hotspots lopend of met openbaar vervoer gemakkelijk te bereiken.

localizedReview.comments: Pleasant, complete, clean apartment, ideal location. Shops and restaurants cafes just around the corner. All hotspots can be reached easily on foot or by public transportation.

reviews.comments: I stayed at the apartment for several days and enjoyed it very much. The co-host, Mirela, was very responsive to all my questions and she gave very detailed check in-instructions. The apartment was absolutely spotless and is in a fantastic location. It is within 10 minutes walking distance to the major sites and very close to bus lines, making it easy to get around the city. Right outside of the building is a square that has a market and several restaurants, and there are many other restaurants within just a few blocks. I would definitely stay at this property again.

Mia's place was perfect for my stay in Tirana.
Check in was easy and the host was really helpful.
It was walking distance from all the main sights and in a nice neighborhood.
I would definitely come here again if I come back to Tirana :)
Very clean, bright and comfortable space. The location could not be better. Highly recommended

The airco in this appartment was our lifesaver during our stay! very nice, clean appartment that's close to many awesome things in the city. every museum is half an hour walking distance with many shops and restaurants on the way. if we come back to Albania, no doubt in my mind we'll pick this appartment again.

Beliggenheden rigtig god, selvom den ligger centralt er der relativt roligt.
Havde stor fornøjelse af altanen.

The location is really good, even though it's centrally located, it's relatively quiet.
Enjoyed the balcony.

reviews.comments: Super schöne Unterkunft, freundliche Kommunikation & schnelle Antwort!

localizedReview.comments: Super nice place, friendly communication & quick response!

reviews.comments: Mia's place feels roomy and we enjoyed having space for our bags, having seating and a small dining area. The balcony gives you more room too. It is within easy walking distance of the town and tourist spots. Many restaurants close by. Mia communicated clearly and instructions for check in were very easy to follow. We arrived by bus to TEG bus station (East Mall) and easily got a bus from there into Tirana. The apartment was then only a 7 minute walk from our stop in Tirana.

I loved Mia’s place.
It was comfortable, clean, had a great shower and an amazingly large balcony.
The location was perfect. Close to amenities and the center of town.
I would stay there again.
Looks just like the photos and is walking distance to the main attractions. Check in was super easy and the instructions were very clear. Would definitely recommend Mia’s home for a stay in Tirana!
